wrapper classes provides a way to use primitive data types(int, boolean, etc..) as objects
since the primitive data types cannot be directly used as objects that's why wrapper classes come into picture
a class that wraps a primitive data types into an object is called wrapper class in java
	primitive datatypes										wrapper class
		char												   character
		byte												   byte
		short												   short
		int 												   integer
		long												   long
		float												   float